  if(dets.deltaY>0){
    console.log("seedha scrolling")
  }
    else{
      console.log("ulta scrolling")
    }
})
****************
use section tag it is seo friendly
*********************************
margin: auto is a simple and effective way to center a block-level element horizontally when its width is specified
      margin: 0 auto; /* Automatically sets equal left and right margins */
float allows you to align block-level elements to the left or right of their container
      float: right; /* Aligns element to the right */

    CSS Flexbox provides precise control over the alignment of child elements, including centering them both horizontally and vertically
.flex-container {
      display: flex; /* Enables flexbox */
      justify-content: center; /* Aligns children horizontally */
      align-items: center; /* Aligns children vertically */
      height: 200px;
      background-color: lightgray;
    }


The text-align property aligns inline content (like text or inline elements) inside a block container. It doesn't apply to block-level elements directly.
